parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) and Collision Mitigation System (CMS) Activation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the AEB and CMS can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake or stop, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes or stops without warning
often with a flashing "BRAKE" warning on the dashboard
and/or a sudden loss of speed. This can occur when there are no obstacles or vehicles in front of the vehicle
and sometimes in response to harmless objects such as metal plates
or construction markings on the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the multi-purpose camera can affect the functionality of various safety features, including the AEB and CMS, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The camera failure can cause the AEB and CMS to malfunction
leading to unintended braking or stopping of the vehicle.
